        "text": "Friedrich Merz (born 11 November 1955 in Brilon, North Rhine-Westphalia) is a German politician and the current Chancellor of Germany. He studied law at the University of Munich from 1976 to 1981 and began his career as a judge in Saarbr\u00fccken before moving into corporate law. In 1989 he was elected to the European Parliament, and from 1994 to 2009 he represented the Hochsauerland constituency in the Bundestag, where he served as chairman of the CDU/CSU parliamentary group from 2000 to 2002. After stepping back from frontline politics in 2009, Merz pursued a business career, serving as chairman of the supervisory board of BlackRock Germany from 2016 to 2020. He returned to politics and was elected leader of the CDU in January 2022. Following the CDU/CSU's victory in the February 2025 federal election, Merz was elected Chancellor of Germany on 6 May 2025, taking office after a second round of voting in the Bundestag. He is married to Charlotte Merz, a judge, and they have four children.",
