        "text": "A lot of people would say media bias today is less about outright falsehoods and more about framing, emphasis, selective outrage, terminology, and decisions about whose perspective is treated as credible. That is why the problem can feel obvious even when individual articles remain technically accurate.\n\nAt that point, saying that trusting mainstream media is naive is not really an extreme claim. Most major outlets operate within a fairly narrow ideological and cultural framework, and that shapes not only how stories are covered, but which stories are elevated in the first place. People who still treat them as neutral sources are often underestimating how systematic that filtering has become.",
